threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, ARM, EABI4 version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, with debug_info, not stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This binary is a malicious DDoS botnet agent belonging to the Condi family. It maintains host dominance by implementing a process killer that terminates competing malware and network diagnostic tools (netstat, wget, curl, busybox) via /proc monitoring. It further sabotages system recovery by unlinking critical administrative binaries including /sbin/reboot, /sbin/halt, and /sbin/shutdown. The sample features an extensive array of DDoS attack vectors, including TCP SYN/ACK floods, UDP floods (Plain, VSE), and SSDP reflection (using M-SEARCH templates). It includes a self-update mechanism that connects to a hardcoded server (185.176.94.132:80) to download and execute architecture-specific payloads (e.g., top1hbt.arm, top1hbt.mips, top1hbt.x86_64).
